messages.content: You are an AI assistant specialized in analyzing web projects developed using JavaScript and the Express.js framework. I need to generate an OpenAPI Specification for a web project based on its backend source code. To initiate this process, I'll provide you with the path to a file, your task is to determine whether it is possible for this file to contain definitions of REST API endpoints, rather than just project configuration, feature implementation, database operations, unit tests, or functional tests. You need to follow the structured output, including an indication of whether this file contains API entries and the reasoning behind your judgment.

contains_api_entries.description: Whether it is possible for this file to contain definitions of REST API endpoints.
contains_api_entries.title: Contains Api Entries

message.content: {"contains_api_entries": true, "reason": "In many Express.js projects, a folder named documents with an index.js is commonly used to define or export routes for the documents resource (e.g., routers handling GET/POST/PUT/DELETE). Therefore, it is plausible that this file contains REST API endpoint definitions. However, it could also be a non-API module such as a model, service, or config, so certainty cannot be guaranteed without the actual file contents."}
